@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="privacy-policy">
    <section class="policy-details">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>Welcome to [Your Supermarket Web App]. We are committed to protecting your personal information and your right to privacy. If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy notice, or our practices with regards to your personal information, please contact us at privacy</p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect personal information that you provide to us when you register on the website, place an order, subscribe to our newsletter, or contact us. The personal information we collect may include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Name</li>
            <li>Email address</li>
            <li>Phone number</li>
            <li>Billing address</li>
            <li>Shipping address</li>
            <li>Payment information</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect in the following ways:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To facilitate account creation and logon process.</li>
            <li>To manage user accounts and provide customer support.</li>
            <li>To fulfill and manage your orders, payments, returns, and exchanges.</li>
            <li>To send administrative information to you, such as updates, security alerts, and support messages.</li>
            <li>To send you marketing and promotional communications.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Sharing Your Information</h2>
        <p>We do not share, sell, rent or trade your information with third parties for their promotional purposes. We may share your data with service providers who assist us in our business operations, such as payment processors, delivery services, and marketing agencies, under strict contractual obligations to protect your information.</p>

        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>We use administrative, technical, and physical security measures to protect your personal information. However, no electronic transmission over the internet or information storage technology can be guaranteed to be 100% secure, so we cannot promise or guarantee that hackers, cybercriminals, or other unauthorized third parties will not be able to defeat our security and improperly collect, access, steal, or modify your information.</p>

        <h2>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
        <p>We may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to access or store information. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.</p>

        <h2>Your Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to access, correct, update, or delete your personal information. You can exercise these rights by contacting us at privacy</p>

        <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this privacy notice from time to time in order to reflect changes to our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new privacy policy on our website. You are advised to review this privacy policy periodically for any changes.</p>

        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at:</p>
        <p>Email: privacyp>
        <p>Address: [Your Supermarket Web App's Address]</p>
    </section>
</div>

<style>
    .privacy-policy {
        padding: 20px;
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .policy-details h2 {
        font-size: 1.5em;
        margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .policy-details p, .policy-details ul {
        font-size: 1em;
        margin: 10px 0;
    }

    .policy-details ul {
        list-style-type: disc;
        margin-left: 20px;
    }
</style>
